  "time_ut": 1657436305,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d87\u0d9f\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China warns America again",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Foreign Minister Wang Yi told US Secretary of State Anthony Blinken on Saturday that it is China's hope that the United States respects China's foreign and domestic policies, removes economic sanctions and abandons the Cold War mentality.",
        "Blinken, meanwhile, had told reporters that he had pressed Wang over China's refusal to impose sanctions on Russia, apparently to no avail.",
        "Blinken and Wang met a day after a meeting of top diplomats from G20 countries in Indonesia on Saturday.",
        "The meeting came at a critical juncture for Washington-Beijing relations. The meeting came as the FBI warned of \"extensive\" industrial espionage and cybercrime emanating from China, and as US President Joe Biden recently announced that he would fight any attempt by the Chinese military to retake Taiwan.",
        "However, in this meeting, Chinese Foreign Minister Wang said, \"Since the United States has promised that it has no intention of creating a conflict with China, they should respect China's sovereignty and territorial integrity and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.\"",
        "Also, Wang accused the United States of trying to prevent and distort the One China policy, referring to Washington's official view that it recognizes China's sovereignty over Taiwan but does not endorse it."
      ],
